dimir Nabokov





TO: FRANCIS E. MINEKA1

CC, 2 pp.

Ithaca, N.Y.





December 7, 1958

Dear Dean Mineka,

I have been in touch with several friends at different universities and colleges, and the two names I submitted to you are those of two teachers who seem to me to be best suited to substitute for me in the coming term.

Miss Helen Muchnic of Smith is a professor of comparative literature and of Russian literature. She has been at Smith for a number of years, has written at least one book 